<p>How many ml in a tablespoon? Here are the tablespoon to ml, and ml to ta=
blespoon conversions you need, plus a handy online and printable conversion=
 chart.</p>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-image size-large"><img data-recalc-dims=3D"1" fet=
chpriority=3D"high" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"1024" height=3D"640" src=3D=
"https://i0.wp.com/mediterraneantaste.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/08/how-ma=
ny-ml-in-a-tablespoon-2436.jpg?resize=3D1024%2C640&amp;ssl=3D1" alt=3D"pour=
ing olive oil into a tablespoon" class=3D"wp-image-26140"></figure>



<p>How many ml in a tablespoon is a common question in our kitchen. In fact=
, with one of us raised in the US and the other in Italy, and family and co=
okbook recipes from both sides of the pond, we are always converting back a=
nd forth between the imperial-based measuring system and the metric system.=
 After years, you=E2=80=99d think I=E2=80=99d remember more kitchen convers=
ions! But I still search out the same measurement equivalents again and aga=
in. </p>



<p>Hence, I=E2=80=99ve created handy references to our most pressing kitche=
n conversion needs, including <strong>how many ml in a tablespoon</strong>!=
 So no matter what side of the pond your recipe is on, you=E2=80=99ll be ab=
le to quickly get the right measurements.</p>



<p>If you are following a recipe measured in milliliters, it=E2=80=99s very=
 helpful to have a cheatsheet to quickly convert to tablespoons, or vice ve=
rsa. My <strong>online and printable conversion chart</strong> of how many =
ml in a tablespoon, and other common amounts, comes in very handy when your=
 hands are deep in the flour bowl.</p>



<h2 id=3D"faq-the-basics" class=3D"wp-block-heading">FAQ =E2=80=93 The Basi=
cs</h2>



<h3 id=3D"what-does-ml-stand-for" class=3D"wp-block-heading">What does ml s=
tand for?</h3>



<p>Ml is an abbreviation for milliliter. The abbreviation is also written a=
s mL.</p>



<h3 id=3D"what-does-ml-mean" class=3D"wp-block-heading">What does ml mean?<=
/h3>



<p>A <strong>ml, mL, milliliter</strong> or <strong>millilitre</strong>, is=
 a measuring unit of the metric system which means a thousandths of a liter=
, with a liter being the basic unit of <strong>volume</strong>, or capacity=
.</p>



<h3 id=3D"what-is-a-tablespoon" class=3D"wp-block-heading">What is a tables=
poon?</h3>



<p>A tablespoon is a unit of volume commonly used to measure small amounts =
in cooking and baking. A US tablespoon can be considered the same as an imp=
erial tablespoon. </p>



<p><em><br>(tablespoon in photo above comes from this <a class=3D"tasty-lin=
k" rel=3D"nofollow sponsored noopener" target=3D"_blank" data-tasty-links-a=
ppend-disclosure=3D"" href=3D"https://amzn.to/458iwhx">measuring spoon set<=
/a>)</em></p>



<h2 id=3D"how-many-ml-in-a-tablespoon" class=3D"wp-block-heading">How many =
ml in a tablespoon?</h2>



<p>There are <strong>15 ml in a tablespoon</strong>.</p>



<p class=3D"has-background" style=3D"background:linear-gradient(360deg,rgb(=
255,255,255) 0%,rgb(245,244,240) 100%)">The tablespoon is a universal kitch=
en measurement that <strong>generally falls around 15 milliliters around th=
e world</strong>. There can be a small range (usually less than 5ml) betwee=
n tablespoons in different countries, however this tiny amount is generally=
 considered insignificant in cooking.<br><br>The exact volume in a tablespo=
on can also vary based on how you pour it, the type of spoon, design and sh=
ape differences, and material (for instance, plastic=E2=80=99s shape, size =
and accuracy can be affected by heat and time and use). <br><br><strong>Usi=
ng a standardized tablespoon made of a stable material like stainless steel=
 is recommended for accuracy.</strong></p>



<p>(<strong>Need the exact figure? 14.79 ml </strong>(14.7868) is the figur=
e for <strong>ml in a tablespoon</strong> given by the <a href=3D"https://w=
ww.nist.gov/pml/owm/approximate-conversions-us-customary-measures-metric" t=
arget=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopener">NIST</a> (National Institute o=
f Standards and Technology =E2=80=93 Weights &amp; Measures), which is then=
 rounded to 15 ml for cooking measurements.</p>



<h2 id=3D"common-tbsp-to-ml-conversions" class=3D"wp-block-heading">Common =
tbsp to ml conversions</h2>



<p><strong>1 tablespoon to ml? &nbsp;</strong> 1 tbsp =3D 15ml</p>



<p><strong>2 tablespoons to ml? &nbsp;</strong> 2 tbsp =3D 30ml</p>



<p><strong>3 tablespoons to ml? &nbsp;</strong> 3 tbsp =3D 45ml</p>



<p><strong>4 tablespoons to ml? &nbsp;</strong> 4 tbsp =3D 60ml</p>



<p>Here=E2=80=99s a handy tbsp to ml conversion chart with standard convers=
ions going<strong><mark style=3D"background-color:rgba(0, 0, 0, 0)" class=
=3D"has-inline-color has-black-color">up to 16 tbsp (240ml or 1 cup</mark>)=
</strong>.</p>



<h2 id=3D"tablespoon-to-ml-conversion-chart" class=3D"wp-block-heading">Tab=
lespoon to mL Conversion Chart</h2>



<figure class=3D"wp-block-table is-style-regular"><table class=3D"has-black=
