<div class=3D"wp-block-file"><a id=3D"wp-block-file--media-173f70cd-8172-4b=
83-b0a2-73db73fff9fc" href=3D"https://mediterraneantaste.com/wp-content/upl=
oads/2023/08/tbsp-ml-table.pdf" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noreferrer noopene=
r">Get the printable Tablespoon to ml Conversion Chart</a></div>



<p><strong>Hope this helps with your conversions between milliliters and ta=
blespoons!</strong></p>



<p>A tablespoon is a good measuring tool for small amounts in <strong>incre=
ments of 15 milliliters</strong>. With amounts outside of 15 mL increments,=
 alternative measuring tools may be more appropriate (such as smaller measu=
ring spoons, measuring cups, or if you=E2=80=99re measuring water, you coul=
d use a digital scale set to grams, since 1 mL of water equals 1 g).</p>



<h2 id=3D"common-ml-to-tbsp-conversions" class=3D"wp-block-heading">Common =
ml to tbsp conversions</h2>



<p class=3D"has-medium-font-size"><strong>How many tablespoons do I need?</=
strong></p>



<ul class=3D"wp-block-list">
<li><strong>15 ml is equal to how many tablespoons? (15 ml to tbsp) </stron=
g><br><br>15 milliliters is equivalent to: 1 tbsp</li>



<li><strong>20 ml is equal to how many tablespoons?</strong> <strong>(20 ml=
 into tablespoons) </strong><br><br>20 milliliters is equivalent to: 1.35 t=
bsp / 1 tbsp + 1 tsp (teaspoon) / 3 tsp </li>



<li><strong>How much is 30 ml in tablespoons?</strong> <strong>(30 ml into =
tablespoons)</strong><br><br>30 milliliters is equivalent to: 2 tbsp</li>
</ul>



